12/06/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The World Bank's board has approved a $19.4m Natural Resources Development Project for Albania, according to a statement from the Bank's office in Tirana Friday (10 June). 
The Bank will provide a $5m grant under the Global Environment Facility Trust Fund; other donors, including the Swedish International Development Co-operation Agency, will provide the rest. 
The project is aimed at reducing poverty and fighting land erosion in Albania's mountainous regions. 
(Albanian News - 11/06/05)
